body:
The official TypeScript SDK for Model Context Protocol (MCP) development, providing comprehensive tools for building both servers and clients.

## Installation
```bash
npm install @modelcontextprotocol/sdk
```

## Key Features

### Server Development
- **Easy Registration**: Simple methods for tools, resources, and prompts
- **Type Safety**: Full TypeScript support with Zod schema validation
- **Dynamic Servers**: Add/remove capabilities at runtime with auto-notifications
- **Resource Templates**: Dynamic resources with parameter substitution
- **Sampling Support**: Servers can request LLM completions from clients
- **Context-Aware Completions**: Intelligent argument auto-completion

### Client Development
- **Full Protocol Support**: Complete MCP client implementation
- **Multiple Transports**: stdio, Streamable HTTP, SSE compatibility
- **Connection Management**: Automatic protocol handling and lifecycle events

### Transport Options
1. **stdio Transport**: Perfect for CLI tools and local development
2. **Streamable HTTP**: Remote servers with session management, CORS support
3. **SSE Transport**: Legacy compatibility mode

## Quick Start Examples

### Basic Server
```typescript
import { McpServer } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/mcp.js";
import { StdioServerTransport } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js";
import { z } from "zod";

const server = new McpServer({
  name: "demo-server",
  version: "1.0.0"
});

// Register a tool
server.registerTool("add", {
  title: "Addition Tool",
  description: "Add two numbers",
  inputSchema: { a: z.number(), b: z.number() }
}, async ({ a, b }) => ({
  content: [{ type: "text", text: String(a + b) }]
}));

// Register a dynamic resource
server.registerResource(
  "greeting",
  new ResourceTemplate("greeting://{name}", { list: undefined }),
  { title: "Greeting Resource" },
  async (uri, { name }) => ({
    contents: [{ uri: uri.href, text: `Hello, ${name}!` }]
  })
);

const transport = new StdioServerTransport();
await server.connect(transport);
```

### Basic Client
```typescript
import { Client } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/client/index.js";
import { StdioClientTransport } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/client/stdio.js";

const client = new Client({
  name: "my-client",
  version: "1.0.0"
});

const transport = new StdioClientTransport({
  command: "node",
  args: ["server.js"]
});

await client.connect(transport);

// Use the client
const result = await client.callTool({
  name: "add",
  arguments: { a: 5, b: 3 }
});
```

### Streamable HTTP Server
```typescript
import express from "express";
import { StreamableHTTPServerTransport } from "@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/streamableHttp.js";

const app = express();
app.use(express.json());

app.post('/mcp', async (req, res) => {
  const transport = new StreamableHTTPServerTransport({
    sessionIdGenerator: () => randomUUID(),
    enableDnsRebindingProtection: true,
    allowedHosts: ['127.0.0.1']
  });

  await server.connect(transport);
  await transport.handleRequest(req, res, req.body);
});
```

## Advanced Features

### Sampling (LLM Requests)
```typescript
server.registerTool("summarize", {
  description: "Summarize text using LLM",
  inputSchema: { text: z.string() }
}, async ({ text }) => {
  const response = await server.server.createMessage({
    messages: [{
      role: "user",
      content: { type: "text", text: `Summarize: ${text}` }
    }],
    maxTokens: 500
  });
  return {
    content: [{ type: "text", text: response.content.text }]
  };
});
```

### Context-Aware Completions
```typescript
server.registerPrompt("team-greeting", {
  argsSchema: {
    department: completable(z.string(), (value) =>
      ["engineering", "sales", "marketing"].filter(d => d.startsWith(value))
    )
  }
}, ({ department, name }) => ({
  messages: [{
    role: "assistant",
    content: { type: "text", text: `Hello ${name}, welcome to ${department}!` }
  }]
}));
```

### Dynamic Server Updates
```typescript
// Tools can be enabled/disabled/updated at runtime
const putMessageTool = server.tool("putMessage", /* config */, /* handler */);
putMessageTool.disable(); // Won't show in listTools
putMessageTool.enable();  // Now available again
putMessageTool.update({ /* new config */ }); // Update parameters
putMessageTool.remove();  // Completely remove
```

## Production Features
- **Session Management**: Stateful server support with session IDs
- **CORS Configuration**: Browser-friendly setup with exposed headers
- **DNS Rebinding Protection**: Built-in security features
- **Notification Debouncing**: Efficient bulk updates
- **Error Handling**: Comprehensive error management
- **Testing Integration**: Works with MCP Inspector

## Repository & Resources
- **GitHub**: https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/typescript-sdk
- **NPM Package**: @modelcontextprotocol/sdk
- **Stars**: 9.5k+ (highly popular)
- **Documentation**: https://modelcontextprotocol.io/
- **Examples**: Comprehensive example servers included
- **License**: MIT

## Requirements
- Node.js v18.x or higher
- TypeScript support recommended
- Zod for schema validation
